{{refimprove|date=July 2018}}

The '''Fédération nationale des transporteurs routiers''' (FNTR: in [[English language|English]], National Federation of [[Road Transport]]) is a [[France|French]] [[Employers’ association|employers' association]] representing [[transport]] companies. Created in 1933, its goal is to defend and promote its members, including the long-term health of firms in the French [[trucking]] sector.

