'''Theresa Park''' (born 1967) is a New York-based [[literary agent]].<ref name="Sambuchino2011">{{cite book|last=Sambuchino|first=Chuck|title=2012 Guide to Literary Agents|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GuYFdoessroC&pg=PA233|accessdate=7 March 2012|date=2011-09-06|publisher=Writer's Digest Books|isbn=978-1-59963-229-2|pages=233–}}</ref> She discovered and represents several internationally best-selling authors, including [[Nicholas Sparks]] and [[Debbie Macomber]], among others.

She is a graduate of [[Harvard Law School]], and originally worked as a corporate attorney in Silicon Valley.

In 1994, she joined [[Sanford J. Greenburger Associates]] as a literary agent. In 2005, she began her own literary agency, Park Literary.<ref>http://www.publishersmarketplace.com/members/ParkLiterary/</ref>

